    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"245476\">Quinn Culver</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/113489-new-members/topic/Critique.20proof.202*x.20.E2.89.A0.203.20in.20.E2.84.A4/near/541311472\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>doability by us</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>The problem with this is that 1. well I am not you, so I don't know what you have learnt and haven't learnt; and 2. the shorter proofs here use \"other tactics\" and \"other theorems\" that you hadn't learnt, but since they have showed you these new tools, now you have learnt them, so now it's doable by you. None of the alternatives are in any sense \"mechanically hard\", so all of them would still fit in the \"doability\" bill.</p>",
        "id": 541327043,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1758746311
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"245476\">Quinn Culver</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/113489-new-members/topic/Critique.20proof.202*x.20.E2.89.A0.203.20in.20.E2.84.A4/near/541311472\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>2x must be even, while 3 is odd</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>here's how to do the first part shorter:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℤ</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≠</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">by_contra</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">g</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Even</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Int</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">even_mul</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">left</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">norm_num</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Odd</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">norm_num</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">g</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">at</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h1</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">contradiction</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 541327568,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1758746552
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>the new trick to learn here is that <code>Int.even_mul</code> (which you have used above) is an iff, and that you can <code>rw</code> using iffs.</p>",
        "id": 541327631,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1758746578
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>and personally I would want to add one more step:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℤ</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≠</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">by_contra</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">g</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Even</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Int</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">even_mul</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">left</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">norm_num</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Odd</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">norm_num</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">g</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">←</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Int</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">not_odd_iff_even</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">at</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h1</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">contradiction</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>the new thing added here is <code>← Int.not_odd_iff_even</code>, which I think makes the logic clearer (you're explicitly using the fact that even iff not odd, which is obvious to a human, but lean only reads the symbols \"even\" and \"odd\" and doesn't know what they \"intuitively\" mean)</p>",
        "id": 541328030,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1758746771
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>here the new trick is <code>←</code> inside the <code>rw</code>, which means \"do this but use the opposite direction\"</p>",
        "id": 541328086,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1758746794
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"307953\">@Ruben Van de Velde</span> and <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"110064\">@Kenny Lau</span> : thanks very much for the clear explanations.</p>",
        "id": 541329685,
        "sender_full_name": "Matteo Bianchetti",
        "timestamp": 1758747538
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Kenny was already getting there, but it's simpler not to mention <code>Odd</code> at all-</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℤ</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≠</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">by_contra</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">g</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Even</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Int</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">even_mul</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">left</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">norm_num</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">¬</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Even</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">norm_num</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">g</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">at</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h1</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">contradiction</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 541332790,
        "sender_full_name": "Ruben Van de Velde",
        "timestamp": 1758748823
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And you can also use a more specialized lemma:</p>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"644391\">@loogle</span> Even (2 * _)</p>",
        "id": 541332900,
        "sender_full_name": "Ruben Van de Velde",
        "timestamp": 1758748892
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"search\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f50d\" role=\"img\" title=\"search\">:search:</span> <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Parity.html#even_two_mul\">even_two_mul</a></p>",
        "id": 541332902,
        "sender_full_name": "loogle",
        "timestamp": 1758748893
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Even</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">even_two_mul</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 541332924,
        "sender_full_name": "Ruben Van de Velde",
        "timestamp": 1758748904
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>indeed, <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"883399\">@Matteo Bianchetti</span> one of the very useful skills you can learn is how to use loogle</p>",
        "id": 541333167,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1758749047
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>loogle has two modes:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>if you want to guess some parts of the <strong>name</strong> of the theorem, include those parts in quotation marks, like <code>\"even\", \"two\", \"mul\"</code></li>\n<li>if you want to guess the <strong>shape</strong> of the theorem, you can use <code>_</code> as holes, and insert the relevant parts in the <strong>statement</strong> of the theorem, so like <code>Even, 2 * _</code></li>\n</ol>",
        "id": 541333310,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1758749121
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(and you can combine them!)</p>",
        "id": 541333325,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1758749128
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>for reference, the theorem is (a bit simplified):<br>\n<code>theorem even_two_mul (a : α) : Even (2 * a)</code><br>\nby the \"name\" I'm referring to the <code>even_two_mul</code> part, and by the \"shape\" I am referring to the <code>(a : α) -&gt; Even (2 * a)</code> part, which is the part that occurs after the name (it can be before or after colon)</p>",
        "id": 541333738,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1758749332
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks again very much <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"307953\">@Ruben Van de Velde</span>  and <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"110064\">@Kenny Lau</span> . Wonderful answers and wonderful pointer to loogle. I did not know about it and I am going to use it a lot.</p>",
        "id": 541344431,
        "sender_full_name": "Matteo Bianchetti",
        "timestamp": 1758756557
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"883399\">@Matteo Bianchetti</span> here's another proof, which I argue is a bit more informative mathematically because the <code>¬ Even 3 := by norm_num</code> is doing most of the work above.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Tactic</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Int</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≠</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">obtain</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Int</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">lt_or_le</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">apply</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ne_of_gt</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Int</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">lt_iff_add_one_le</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">at</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">calc</span>\n<span class=\"w\">      </span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">decide</span>\n<span class=\"w\">      </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≤</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">gcongr</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">apply</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ne_of_lt</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">calc</span>\n<span class=\"w\">      </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≤</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">gcongr</span>\n<span class=\"w\">      </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">decide</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Here, the key lemma is <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Int.lt_iff_add_one_le#doc\">docs#Int.lt_iff_add_one_le</a>. This is one way you might go about showing that <code>3</code> is not even in practice.</p>",
        "id": 541518679,
        "sender_full_name": "Jireh Loreaux",
        "timestamp": 1758824002
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Why am I proving this?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Int</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≠</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">intro</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">congrArg</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">%</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">simp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">at</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">this</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
